<br>
There are three sages.  Each sage has two assistants.  Each assistant is to receive research items from one of the Sage's two colleagues.<br>
<br>
Sages:<br>
. Evil: Gunyth<br>
.   Device Function: Fashion Notes from Spells<br>
.   Assistants:<br>
.     Onerelin  (show him items from: Balic)<br>
.     Xesri     (show him items from: Xerlin)<br>
.<br>
. Neutral: Balic<br>
.   Device Function:  Combine Runes and Words for ?<br>
.   Assistants:<br>
.     Winon     (show him items from: Gunyth)<br>
.     Tenada    (show him items from: Xerlin)<br>
<br>
. Good: Xerlin<br>
.   Device Function:  Extract Spell from Items with Charges <br>
.   Assistants:<br>
.     Boloen    (show him items from: Balic)<br>
.     Acomar    (show him items from: Gunyth)<br>
<br>
<br>
Notice that research items from a given Sage are to be shown to one assistant of each colleague. <br>
<br>
The quest dialog has general directions along these lines, these being applicable to all three different uses of the Sage Box:<br>
1.  Use Sage Box to Create a new item from various components<br>
2.  Show that item to the Sage who instructed you in that particular use of the Sage Box.<br>
3.  Take what the Sage gives you and show it to a specific assistant of one of the two other sages.<br>
<br>
We have solved the Sage Box as Sage Gunyth intends for us to use it.<br>
<br>
We know that showing the notes (B, C, D, E) to Gunyth result in Charged Magic Items (Amulet of Knowledge, Book of Forgotten Magic, Arcane Quill, Gem of Flowing Breath).  Interestingly, Gunyth refuses note A.<br>
<br>
Showing the Charged Magic Items to Assistant Acomar results in a mundane treasure.  Almost everyone agrees, myself included, that this is the wrong path for these items.  It is likely that they are to be used as components in the Sage Box under Xerlin's method, without ever showing them to an assistant.  Can anyone verify what Assistant Winon has to say about the Charged Magic Items?<br>
<br>
Since it has become clear that the process of creating 'notes' by combining spells is an expensive process (particularly the 'A' note), I think it would be in all of our best interests to carefully record which assistant (by name) you are handing the items to at each step, so we have a clear understanding of the proper paths required and so that we avoid expensive missteps in the future.<br>
<br>
I think our next course of action would be:  Show note 'A' to Winon and/or Acomar.  But which one?  My guess would be Acomar, because we are instructed show him items from Gunyth, the only items we get from Gunyth are the Charged Magic Items and Note 'A', and since showing the Charged Magic Items to Acomar is apparently the wrong items to show him, then that leave only note 'A' as the proper thing to show him.<br>
<br>
Since this is a very painful step, it would be nice to do the following first:<br>
1.  Document the result of handing one of the Charged Magic Items to Assistant Winon.  If Winon does return a significant item as a result, it would suggest that note 'A' should be shown to Acomar first.<br>
2.  Document the result of handing one of the Charged Magic Items to any of the four assistants that are not on one of the proscribed paths (Onerlin, Xesri, Tenada, Boloen).  Hopefully, they reject the items, as they are not on one of the proper paths.<br>
2.  Since Sage Gunyth returns note 'A' when given note 'A', and we must give this note to one of the two assistants Winon or Acomar, it may be instructive to document what happens when we give one of the other, easier to obtain notes (say D or E), to these assistants (Acomar or Winon).  Its not clear how useful this information would be.  They could refuse the item, reward you with a mundane treasure, or - hopefully - with a significant step in the quest process, say a rune or a page.<br>
<br>
Ultimately, it seems that someone will have to hand in the unique 'A' note to Winon and/or Acomar.  I seriously hope that this will result in a new research component (Word or Page for example) to be combined in the Sage Box in one of the other fashions.  Whatever happens, it is clearly the next logical step in the quest.<br>
<br>
If the result of this is more mundane items, then heaven help us as there are a lot of old world Words and Pages that need combining.<br>
<br>
Erun<br>
59 Mage<br>
SBoW<br>
E'Ci<br>
