<br>
Unfortunately, my results did not turn out as well as I had hoped, but here they are anyway.<br>
<br>
For the sake of brevity, I will use the following definitions:<br>
<br>
VT (Vendor Trash):  When an assistant rewards you with gem/jewelry in exchange for a research component this is called VT.<br>
Proper Path:  The 'Proper Path' is that relationship between a Sage's assistants and that Sage's two colleagues.  You may reference my above post for explicit relationships.<br>
Charged Magic Item:  One of the items that Gunyth returns in exchange for notes (B,C,D,E)<br>
<br>
<br>
In the following statements, I did NOT test every possible case.  I assumed that a reaction for note 'B' would be the same reaction expected for notes (C,D,E), similarly with the Charged Magic Items.<br>
<br>
0.  We have already learned previously that when giving a Charged Magic Item to Acomer, he rewards you with VT.<br>
<br>
1.  I gave a Charged Magic Item to Winon.  He refused it.<br>
<br>
2.  I gave a Charged Magic Item to each assistant outside the 'Proper Path' from Gunyth.  They all refused it.<br>
<br>
3.  I gave a note to Acomer, which was NOT note 'A'.  He accepted it and rewarded me with VT.<br>
<br>
4.  I gave a note to Winon, which was NOT note 'A',  He accepted it and rewarded me with VT.<br>
<br>
5.  I gave a note, which was NOT note 'A', to each assistant outside of the 'Proper Path' from Gunyth.  They all refused it.<br>
<br>
6.  I gave note 'A' to Acomer, He refused it.<br>
<br>
7.  I gave note 'A' to Winon, He refused it.<br>
<br>
8.  I gave note 'A' to each assistant outside the 'Proper Path' from Gunyth.  They all refused it.<br>
<br>
Conclusions:<br>
<br>
From the results 0 and 1, it seems clear that Charged Magic Items coming out of Gunyth's Laboratory are intended to go to Xelrin's Laboratory, but not to Balic's Laboratory.  This is what we all assumed anyway, but its nice to see verification in this fashion.<br>
<br>
From result 2, it is clear that the defined notion of 'Proper Path' is indeed valid.  This is reinforced by results 5 and 8.<br>
<br>
From results 3,4,6,7, it is clear that there is something signicantly unique about note 'A' that separates it from the other notes.  We already knew that because Gurnyth will exchange all notes for a Charged Magic Item with the exception of note 'A' which he refuses.  This is the single most disturbing aspect of this quest that I can see at this time.  The quest has maintained a very clean symmetry up until this point, and it is difficult to see any reason for it.  I encourage speculation on this point.<br>
<br>
From results 3,4,5,6,7,8, it is clear that nobody at all is interested in note 'A'.<br>
<br>
<br>
Finally, these results boil down to:<br>
<br>
1.  Only Sage Xelrin is interested in Charged Magic Items.  (We already kinda knew that anyway).<br>
<br>
2.  Only notes (B,C,D,E) and not 'A' are of interest to Sage Gunyth's colleagues, as evidenced by the interest shown by their assistants.<br>
<br>
3.  BOTH his colleagues are interested in these notes (B,C,D,E).<br>
<br>
<br>
Speculation:<br>
<br>
I have been going on the assumption that if an action has resulted in a reward (even simply VT/XP), then the designers are hinting that the direction one is taking is close to the true correct direction, while when an object is compeltely refused by an NPC, then this is hint to look el;sewhere.  This assumption may or may not be valid.<br>
<br>
The reward associated with giving Charged Magic Items to the assistant in Xerlin's laboratory indicates that, while you are not supposed to give the Charged Magic Item directly to the assistant, you are at least going in the right direction.  You are encouraged to bring the Charged Magic Item into the laboratory and experiment with it yourself (i.e. put it in the Sage Box with other things, as the sage described in his monologue, and push the 'combine' button).<br>
<br>
The complete stonewall associated with trying to bring the Charged Magic Items into Balic's laboratory indicates that this is the improper path, and one should look elsewhere.<br>
<br>
But, you will notice, that if this assumption is granted, then that would indicate that the 'notes' are to be employed in BOTH Balic's and Xerlin's laboratory (Sage Box).<br>
<br>
While I'm confused over the anomolous 'A' note, I am willing to temporarily overlook that and suggest that maybe combining a note (B,C,D,E) in the Sage Box with a Rune might be something to look at.<br>
<br>
<br>
Any of you who have made it this far must be either really bored or actually very interested in seeing this quest through to it's completion, as I am.  Please feel free to speculate.  My assumptions may be wildly optimistic and my conclusions may be overreaching to an extreme.  Maybe Im going down the completely wrong path.<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
Erun<br>
59 Mage<br>
SBoW<br>
E'ci<br>
